&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resource planning and procurement strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Market entry assessments and due diligence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Transmission access and congestion analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Capacity accreditation and resource adequacy strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Mentor junior staff and contribute to business development through proposal writing and client engagement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree required, advanced degree in a related field (economics, engineering, public policy, energy systems) is a plus;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of professional experience in the electricity sector, with direct experience with ISO/RTO markets (e.g., CAISO, PJM, SPP, ERCOT, MISO, ISO-NE).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to&amp;nbsp;modeling or analytics tools used in electricity markets (e.g., PROMOD, PLEXOS, GridView, ABB, ISO data APIs, etc.) preferred;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of market design and interconnection processes, including: Generation and storage interconnection rules and timelines, Capacity market structures and performance requirements, and Energy market operations, bidding behavior, and congestion management;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with or for utilities, grid operators, project developers

